If you experience the "gc2 has stopped working" error it's because of the Data Execution Prevention of Windows, you have to switch it off for gc2 to work. (Defining gc2.exe as an exception won't work)

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data_Execution_Prevention

This is how you switch DEP off in Vista: (for XP you will have to edit the boot.ini if you're not sure how to do that, consult the interwebs)

The Data Execution Prevention can be switched off by starting cmd with administrator clearance and typing

bcdedit.exe /set {current} nx AlwaysOff

after pressing enter you have to restart the computer then GC2 should work.
